HEADWORD: Bungee jumping
<hw>Bun"gee jump`ing</hw></mhw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>an act of derring-do in which a
person jumps from a high platform, such as a bridge, attached (usually
by the legs) to a bungee cord, which is set to a length that will halt
the drop before the person reaches the surface of the earth or the
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bunghole</ent>⟦br⟧
